          +message-block('По результатам 2022 года КПЭ генерального директора и членов правления преимущественно выполнены/перевыполнены, имеющиеся отклонения незначительны, что обусловлено проведением мероприятий по повышению эффективности деятельности компании. ')
mixin reward-content-EN
  section(data-aos="fade-up").reward.mt-section(id="reward-mt")
    .container-content
      .reward__inner
        .reward__top
          h3.reward__title General Director 
          .row
            p.reward__text_top.text_big In order to motivate the General Director to improve the management efficiency and to solve the strategic tasks set by the shareholders and the Board of Directors, the company has the effective Regulations on General Director Rewards. 
          .reward__bottom 
            .reward__item 
              .reward__item-top
                p.reward__item-description.description_big The document provides for the following rewards:
                ul.list
                  each item in ['Quarter-end bonus','Year-end bonus','Outstanding performance bonus.',]
                    li
                      +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                      p.text.list__text=item 
              .reward__item-bottom 
                p.text.reward__text The resolution on rewarding the General Director for the reporting period is adopted by the Board of Directors upon reviewing the General Director’s budget performance report for the corresponding period. The General Director’s performance assessment results are also taken into account. Performance means meeting the qualitative, quantitative and key performance indicators (KPI).
                p.text.reward__text The KPI list, weight and targets for the General Director of UTLC ERA are focused on the company’s operating model, which is based on all transit traffic operations in direct rail or mixed rail and sea service through the territories of at least two shareholders via the border or port stations, including, but not limited to: Dostyk, Altynkol, Brest, Bruzhi, Svislach, Mamonovo, Zheleznodorozhny, Kaliningrad-Sortirovochny (Kaliningrad Trade Sea Port), Baltiysk (Baltyisk Port), Buslovskaya, and Wärtsilä, Finland.
            .reward__item 
              .reward__item-top
                p.reward__item-description.description_big The integral assessment of the general director’s performance by the Board of Directors is performed in the following areas:
                ul.list
                  li
                    +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                    p.text.list__text Corporate discipline','High quality and timely budget development for the current and future reporting periods
                  li
                    +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                    p.text.list__text Procurement planning and implementation
                  li
                    +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                    p.text.list__text Contract management and execution
                  li
                    +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                    p.text.list__text Interaction with the Board of Directors
              .reward__item-bottom 
                p.text.reward__text The list of areas is subject to change by the Board of Directors. Performance in each area is assessed according to a four-point grading scale (excellent — 3 points; good — 2; satisfactory — 1; unsatisfactory — 0), with an average grade percentage subsequently calculated for all areas.
                p.text.reward__text Outstanding performance is rewarded as resolved by the Board of Directors on the basis of the General Director’s proposal with the attached performance calculations and supporting indicators. Outstanding performance may be rewarded throughout the reporting period as resolved by the Board of Directors, but no more frequently than once in a quarter. 
            .reward__item 
              .reward__item-top
                p.reward__item-description.description_big The General Director’s KPIs are approved by the Board of Directors on an annual basis. The following KPIs were approved for 2022 (Minutes No. 46):
                ul.list
                  li
                    +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                    p.text.list__text Meeting the net profit indicator (weight: 30%)','Meeting the return on sales indicator (weight: 20%)
                  li
                    +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                    p.text.list__text Meeting the transit container traffic volume indicator, which is defined as the ratio of actual transit container traffic volume in the reporting period to the volume according to the budget, and calculated in percent (weight: 40%)
                  li
                    +mark-text-svg.list-svg
                    p.text.list__text Integral assessment of the director’s performance by the members of the Company’s Board of Directors with a 10% weight
              .reward__item-bottom 
                p.text.reward__text For the first three KPIs, a target performance range is defined, with a 0, 0.5 or 1 coefficient to be applied within this range.
  section(data-aos="fade-up").reward-rule.mt-section(id="reward-rule")
